title: Lost Things
author: Mr_Tommytoms
pages:
#- Lost Things-

Do you know when you've lost something- like your favorite t-shirt or a set of keys- and while looking for it, you come across something else that you missed but have long since forgotten? Well whatever it was, there
#- was a point where you decided to stop searching, maybe because it was no longer required or a new replacement was found. It is almost as if it never existed in the first place- until that moment of rediscorvery, a flash recognition.
#- Everyone has one. An inventory of lost things waiting to be found. Yearning to be acknowledged for the worth they once held in your life.

I think this is where I belong. Among all of your other lost things. A crumpled note at the bottom of an old 
#- drawer, or an old photograph pressed between the pages of a book. 

I hope one day you will find me and remember what I once meant to you. 


#- This is a story from Lang Leav, and it hits close to home for me. I had to share. 

Be kind to each other.
#- 